As requested by the KMT, the meeting was broadcast live on TV.
Also on hand were Yu Shyi-kun, secretary-general to the president;
Chen Che-nan, deputy secretary-general to the president; Lin
Feng-cheng, secretary-general of the Central Committee of the KMT;
and KMT spokesman Jason Hu.

Asked about the reasons for the DPP government's
worse-than-expected performance, 36.7 percent cited "inexperience";
23.81 percent said the new government lacks vision and direction;
17.69 percent blamed the new government's lack of coordination;
and 13.61 percent cited the new government's "policy inconsistence
and incoherence."

The committee's main missions will be planning the nation's
science and technology development policy; planning the application
and integration of national science and technology resources;
planning a national science and technology development framework;
cultivating science and technology talent; as well as other functions
yet to be assigned by the president.

